  <roomsDescription><![CDATA[<ul>
<ul>
<li>The bedrooms are simply but comfortably furnished and many are large enough to have an extra single sofa-bed, if required.</li>
<li>Most bedrooms have balcony and most have private en suite facilities. Hairdryers are provided in each room</li>
<li>Two members of the Cafe Tirol staff live in the chalet</li>
</ul>
</ul>
<p><strong>Accommodation Summary</strong></p>
<p><strong>Lower Ground Floor</strong></p>
<p>Ski and boot room</p>
<p><strong>Ground Floor</strong></p>
<p>Entrance and stairs to chalet</p>
<p><strong>First Floor</strong></p>
<p>Dining room and newly built lounge with TV</p>
<p><strong>Rooms 1, 2, 3, 6</strong> Austrian Twins with shower/wc/balcony*</p>
<p><strong>Room 4</strong> Double with shower/wc balcony†</p>
<p><strong>Room 5</strong> Single with shower/wc/balcony*</p>
<p><strong>Second Floor</strong></p>
<p><strong>Rooms 7*, 9, 10</strong> Austrian Twins with shower/wc/balcony</p>
<p><strong>Room 8</strong> Austrian Twin with shared shower/wc*</p>
<p><strong>Room 11</strong> Single with shared shower/wc*</p>
<p>*Rooms 8 and 11 share shower/wc in corridor. Rooms 1, 2, 3, 7 and 8 have an extra single sofa bed that can sleep an adult. Room 5 can sleep 1 adult and 1 child on a sofa bed. †Room 4 is available for single use.</p>
<p>Austrian twin beds are one large bed frame containing two single mattresses, both with separate duvets and linen sets, that cannot be separated.</p>]]></roomsDescription>
